---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="The Framework"
  description="The Poesis SAFe Agentic Framework — the open, Apache-2.0 BUILD layer that turns governed GSM definitions into runnable code."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Open · Apache-2.0</p>
      <h1>The SAFe Agentic Framework.</h1>
      <p class="lead">The open BUILD layer: SAFe-shaped multi-agent orchestration that turns governed GSM definitions into runnable code — closing THINK → BUILD → RUN.</p>
      <div class="hero-cta">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://github.com/poesis-cloud">Get it on GitHub</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/standard">See the THINK layer</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid grid-3">
        <div class="card"><h3>Portfolio → iteration</h3><p>Orchestrators across portfolio, program, and iteration tempos, with a specialist bench and a deterministic harness.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>The generative bridge</h3><p>Governed definitions become running systems — making GSM's promise, “definitions that generate systems”, literally true.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>An open magnet</h3><p>Free and open for the AI-engineering / agentic community — and a funnel into the Poesis stack and services.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--soft">
    <div class="container center">
      <h2>Close the loop in your own delivery.</h2>
      <p class="lead" style="margin-inline:auto">See how governed definitions become running, observed, self-correcting systems.</p>
      <p><a class="btn btn-primary" href="/contact">Talk to us</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
